Welcome to the Ping-Pong game with Python!

To run this game, you will need Python 3 installed on your computer.

Once you have Python 3 installed, follow these steps:

Download or clone the Ping-Pong game repository from GitHub.

Open your terminal or command prompt and navigate to the Ping-Pong game directory.

Run the game by running the following command:
python main.py

Use the left and right arrow keys to move your paddle and hit the ball back to your opponent.

The game will end when one player reaches 11 points or the ball goes out of bounds.

Enjoy playing Ping-Pong!